name: Surgical Scalpels
description: Precision cutting instruments used for making incisions in tissue during surgery.

name: Hemostats
description: Clamps used to control bleeding by constricting blood vessels or tissues during surgery.

name: Surgical Gloves
description: Sterile gloves worn by medical staff during procedures to maintain sterility.

name: Surgical Masks
description: Worn by surgeons and surgical staff to prevent contamination and protect both the patient and healthcare workers.

name: Surgical Sponges
description: Surgical sponges are sterile absorbent materials used during surgeries to absorb blood and fluids, maintain a clean surgical field, and control bleeding.

name: Surgical blades
description: Surgical blades are precision-cutting tools used in medical procedures for making incisions in tissue with high accuracy.
